  <front>
   <head>TO HENRY.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">fatal form, where'er I go,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Still swims before my sight;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">It dooms the day to restless woe,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Of sleep it robs the night:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">While thou art wandering far away,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">From all such sorrow free;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Forgetting her, who, night and day,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Can think of .</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Yet, be it so! I would not cloud</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Thy days in gloom like mine;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">No .... though my life to grief be vowed,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">May constant bliss be thine!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I'll ne'er by looks, or language, speak</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The pang that preys on me;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor shalt thou, if my heart should break,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Suspect it .</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
